            "title": "Quantum mechanics : detailed historical, mathematical and computational approaches",
            "abstract": [
                "\"This book brings historical perspective of quantum mechanics and quantum chemistry along with detailed mathematical support for the understanding of matrix mechanics, wave mechanics, quantum statistics and quantum chemistry. In order to enhance the learning experience, this book also includes the fundamentals of Fortran and numerical calculations to pave the way for the source codes of several problems of quantum mechanics and quantum chemistry. All these codes are available on the author's website. In addition, there are several proposed exercises and do-it-yourself activities. The main target audience are the students of Physics, Chemistry and Chemical Engineering, as also students and researchers of theoretical physics and chemistry\"--",
                "Basics of Fortran -- Basics of numerical calculation and series -- Linear algebra for quantum mechanics -- Differential equations for quantum mechanics -- Absorption/emission spectroscopy and spectral lines -- Black-body radiation, Einstein and Planck's law -- Bohr, Sommerfeld and the old quantum mechanics -- Heisenberg's matrix quantum mechanics -- Wave packet and de Broglie's wave-particle duality -- Schr\u00f6dinger's wave quantum mechanics -- Applications of matrix and wave quantum mechanics -- Land\u00e9, Pauli, Dirac and spin -- Boltzmann and Fermi-Dirac statistics -- One-particle quantum harmonic oscillator -- Particle in a box -- Particle in a circular motion and angular momentum -- Hydrogen-like atoms and atomic orbitals -- Helium atom, variational method and perturbation theory."
            ],
